    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Corinthians 6 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:1",
      "text": "Working together, we entreat also that you do not receive the grace of God in vain.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:2",
      "text": "For he says, “ At an acceptable time I listened to you. In a day of salvation I helped you.” Behold, now is the acceptable time. Behold, now is the day of salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:3",
      "text": "We give no occasion of stumbling in anything, that our service may not be blamed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:4",
      "text": "but in everything commending ourselves as servants of God: in great endurance, in afflictions, in hardships, in distresses,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:5",
      "text": "in beatings, in imprisonments, in riots, in labors, in watchings, in fastings,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:6",
      "text": "in pureness, in knowledge, in perseverance, in kindness, in the Holy Spirit, in sincere love,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:7",
      "text": "in the word of truth, in the power of God, by the armor of righteousness on the right hand and on the left,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:8",
      "text": "by glory and dishonor, by evil report and good report, as deceivers and yet true,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:9",
      "text": "as unknown and yet well known, as dying and behold — we live, as punished and not killed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:10",
      "text": "as sorrowful yet always rejoicing, as poor yet making many rich, as having nothing and yet possessing all things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:11",
      "text": "Our mouth is open to you, Corinthians. Our heart is enlarged.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:12",
      "text": "You are not restricted by us, but you are restricted by your own affections.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:13",
      "text": "Now in return— I speak as to my children — you also open your hearts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:14",
      "text": "Don’t be unequally yoked with unbelievers, for what fellowship do righteousness and iniquity have? Or what fellowship does light have with darkness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:15",
      "text": "What agreement does Christ have with Belial? Or what portion does a believer have with an unbeliever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:16",
      "text": "What agreement does a temple of God have with idols? For you are a temple of the living God. Even as God said, “ I will dwell in them and walk in them. I will be their God and they will be my people.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:17",
      "text": "Therefore “‘ Come out from among them, and be separate,’ says the Lord. ‘Touch no unclean thing. I will receive you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-corinthians.6.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 6:18",
      "text": "I will be to you a Father. You will be to me sons and daughters,’ says the Lord Almighty.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
